<subSubSection id="C36857FD0F2EFFA7A6A6FD684B43FD76" box="[199,1055,730,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">For a reader’s convenience, the amended Fraser’s key to males of the species of</subSubSection>
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A246FD694B2CFD76" box="[1063,1136,731,754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
<subSubSection id="C36857FD0F2EFFA7A246FD694B30FD76" box="[1063,1132,731,754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="nomenclature">
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A246FD694B30FD76" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1063,1132,731,754]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lestes</taxonomicName>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36857FD0F2EFFA7A20DFD694E0CFB26" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A216FD684A32FD76" authority="Selys, 1862" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1143,1390,730,754]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A216FD684BB7FD76" box="[1143,1259,730,754]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Platylestes</emphasis>
Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A6F6FD4C4EC4FC92" authority="Fraser, 1951" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1951" box="[151,408,766,790]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Sinhalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A6F6FD4C4E53FC92" box="[151,271,766,790]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Sinhalestes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A774FD4C4EC4FC92" author="Fraser, F. C." box="[277,408,766,790]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="61 - 69" refId="ref5002" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1951) Outline of a new classification for the legion Lestes Selys (Order Odonata). Entomological News, 60 (2), 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1951">Fraser, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A7DAFD4C4EA8FC92" box="[443,500,766,790]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A79FFD4C4D07FC92" box="[510,603,766,790]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A404FD4C4D93FC92" box="[613,719,766,790]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A4B8FD4C4C09FC92" box="[729,853,766,790]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A5E9FD4C4CACFC92" box="[904,1008,766,790]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
is reproduced below entirely (in spite of the lack or scarce new information on some species). The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A52EFC904C9BFCBE" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1951" box="[847,967,802,826]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Sinhalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A52EFC904C9BFCBE" box="[847,967,802,826]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Sinhalestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A2FAFC904A70FCBE" author="Fraser, F. C." box="[1179,1324,802,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="61 - 69" refId="ref5002" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1951) Outline of a new classification for the legion Lestes Selys (Order Odonata). Entomological News, 60 (2), 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1951">Fraser (1951)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A33BFC914EBFFCDA" authority="Hagen in Selys, 1862" authorityName="Hagen in Selys" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A33BFC914FA1FCDA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes orientalis</emphasis>
Hagen in Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
after publication of his monograph (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A503FCF44CB9FCDA" author="Fraser, F. C." box="[866,997,838,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refId="ref4932" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1933) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata. Vol. I. Taylor and Francis, London, 423 pp." type="book" year="1933">Fraser 1933</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A597FCF54A74FCDA" authority="Selys, 1891" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1891" box="[1014,1320,838,862]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A597FCF54BFBFCDA" box="[1014,1191,838,862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes bilineatus</emphasis>
Selys, 1891
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A33BFCF54EC8FC06" authority="Schmidt, 1964" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A33BFCF54FADFC06" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes malaisei</emphasis>
Schmidt, 1964
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A423FCD84DF7FC06" box="[578,683,874,898]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, are not included as most probably belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A2C9FCD84AC0FC06" authority="Fraser, 1922" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1922" box="[1192,1436,874,898]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Indolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A2C9FCD84A48FC06" box="[1192,1300,874,898]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Indolestes</emphasis>
Fraser, 1922
</taxonomicName>
(see, respectively, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A73CFC3C4D51FC22" author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[349,525,910,934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="229 - 256" refId="ref5230" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1960) On the identity of some little known southeast Asiatic Odonata in European museums described by De Selys Longchamps. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 38, 229 - 256." type="journal article" year="1960">Lieftinck (1960)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A423FC3C4DA4FC22" author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[578,760,910,934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="561 - 575" refId="ref5092" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2018) Rediscovery of Lestes nigriceps Fraser, 1924 (Odonata: Lestidae) in eastern Cambodia. Zootaxa, 4526 (4), 561 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.4.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Kosterin (2018))</bibRefCitation>
. Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A55FFC3D4CF5FC22" authorityName="Selys Apices" authorityYear="1891" box="[830,937,910,934]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodalis">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A55FFC3D4CF5FC22" box="[830,937,910,934]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. nodalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(occurring at least in Lower 
<collectingCountry id="F36544E60F2EFFA7A280FC3C4A16FC22" box="[1249,1354,910,934]" name="Myanmar" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A3E6FC3D4FA2FC4D" authorityName="in Lahiri" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garoensis">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A3E6FC3D4FA2FC4D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. garoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are included. The volume and limits of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A573FC004CDAFC4E" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[786,902,946,970]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A573FC004CDAFC4E" box="[786,902,946,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Platylestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear and the attribution of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A374FC014ACFFC4E" authorityName="Hagen in Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1301,1427,947,970]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praemorsus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A374FC014ACFFC4E" box="[1301,1427,947,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">praemorsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group to either 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A75FFC654EDDFC6A" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[318,385,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A75FFC654EDDFC6A" box="[318,385,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A7C6FC644D47FC6A" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[423,539,982,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Platylestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A7C6FC644D47FC6A" box="[423,539,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Platylestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is equivocal (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A4D2FC644C0EFC6A" author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[691,850,982,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="561 - 575" refId="ref5092" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2018) Rediscovery of Lestes nigriceps Fraser, 1924 (Odonata: Lestidae) in eastern Cambodia. Zootaxa, 4526 (4), 561 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.4.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Kosterin 2018</bibRefCitation>
); here they are referred to in 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A2EEFC654B8EFC6A" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1167,1234,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A2EEFC654B8EFC6A" box="[1167,1234,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
just in accordance with the current practice. Also I abstain from inclusion of subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A5C7FC494A01FB96" authority="Hagen in Selys, 1862" authorityName="Hagen in Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[934,1373,1018,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praemorsus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A5C7FC494B32FB96" box="[934,1134,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes praemorsus</emphasis>
Hagen in Selys, 1862
</taxonomicName>
since this matter is insufficiently resolved. The measurement ranges for 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A53BFBAD4BD2FBB2" authority="Fraser, 1923" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1923" box="[858,1166,1054,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorothea">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A53BFBAD4B5FFBB2" box="[858,1027,1054,1078]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes dorothea</emphasis>
Fraser, 1923
</taxonomicName>
are given as extended by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A6F6FBF04E76FBDE" author="Lahiri, A. R." box="[151,298,1090,1114]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" pagination="1 - 402" refId="ref5140" refString="Lahiri, A. R. (1987) Studies on the odonate fauna of Meghalaya. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, Miscellaneous publication, Occasional paper No. 99, 1 - 402." type="book chapter" year="1987">Lahiri (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. Fraser’s “thorax” is replaced by a more correct “synthorax”. Fraser’s statement “Thorax immaculate” for 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A6F6FBD54EEDFBFA" authority="Selys, 1891" authorityName="Selys Apices" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,433,1126,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodalis">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A6F6FBD54E73FBFA" box="[151,303,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Lestes nodalis</emphasis>
Selys, 1891
</taxonomicName>
contradicts his own description of this species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2EFFA7A5CCFBD44B72FBFA" author="Fraser, F. C." box="[941,1070,1126,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" refId="ref4932" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1933) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata. Vol. I. Taylor and Francis, London, 423 pp." type="book" year="1933">Fraser 1933</bibRefCitation>
) and corrected to “Synthorax with few black spots”.
</subSubSection>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection id="C36857FD0F2EFFA6A6F6FB7F4AC1FD8B" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" type="key">
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2EFFA7A6F6FB7F4AC0FB7B" blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1436,1229,1280]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">1. Synthorax without metallic markings ...................................................................... 2</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2EFFA7A683FAB54AC0FA99" blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1287,1309]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Synthorax with green metallic antehumeral stripes........................................................... 6</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2EFFA7A6F6FA974AC0FAD3" blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[151,1436,1317,1368]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">2. Pterostigma unicolorous................................................................................ 3</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2EFFA7A683FAED4AC0FAF0" blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" box="[226,1436,1375,1397]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">Pterostigma bicolorous................................................................................ 4</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2EFFA7A6F6FACF4AC1FA49" blockId="2.[151,1437,1229,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">
3. No broad black dorsal stripe on synthorax (middorsal carina can be finely stressed with black); occiput reddish brown to creamy white; paraprocts extend at most to 1/3 of expanded part of cerci................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2EFFA7A28FFA0A4E19FA6F" authority="Hag. Synthorax" authorityName="Hag. Synthorax" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinnus">
<emphasis id="B906D8640F2EFFA7A28FFA0A4A34FA49" box="[1262,1384,1464,1485]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="299">L. concinnus</emphasis>
Hag. 
