<subSubSection id="C36857FD0F2FFFA6A6F6FD884CDBFCCA" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2FFFA6A6F6FD884A10FDD6" blockId="3.[151,1437,570,847]" box="[151,1356,570,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
Naturally, using any key is insufficient to identify tropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C727FF50F2FFFA6A569FD884C3EFDD6" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[776,866,570,594]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Odonata</taxonomicName>
and the full descriptions should be consulted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD04760F2FFFA6A6A6FDED4C34FC82" blockId="3.[151,1437,570,847]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
I should make a clarification on another matter concerned in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2FFFA6A507FDEC4B49FDF3" author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[870,1045,606,631]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="561 - 575" refId="ref5092" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2018) Rediscovery of Lestes nigriceps Fraser, 1924 (Odonata: Lestidae) in eastern Cambodia. Zootaxa, 4526 (4), 561 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.4.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Kosterin (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. Matti Hämäläinen kindly informed me that the number of 366 species described by C.H. Fraser, which I cited in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2FFFA6A5BDFD304BDBFD1F" author="Kosterin, O. E." box="[988,1159,642,667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="561 - 575" refId="ref5092" refString="Kosterin, O. E. (2018) Rediscovery of Lestes nigriceps Fraser, 1924 (Odonata: Lestidae) in eastern Cambodia. Zootaxa, 4526 (4), 561 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.4.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Kosterin (2018)</bibRefCitation>
according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2FFFA6A37BFD304E62FD3B" author="Wasscher, M. &amp; Dumont, H. J." pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="369 - 402" refId="ref5329" refString="Wasscher, M. &amp; Dumont, H. J. (2013) Life and work of Michel Edmond de Selys Lonchamps (1813 - 1900), the founder of Odonatology. Odonatologica, 42 (4), 369 - 402." type="journal article" year="2013">Wasscher &amp; Dumont (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, was strongly underestimated. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE379870F2FFFA6A4E3FD144C6EFD3A" author="Kimmins, D. E." box="[642,818,678,702]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" pagination="173 - 227" refId="ref5038" refString="Kimmins, D. E. (1966) A list of the Odonata types described by F. C. Fraser, now in the British Museum (Natural History). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology, 18 (6), 173 - 227." type="journal article" year="1966">Kimmins (1966)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 562 species group names described by him and although some of them proposed in a subspecific rank, the number of those described as species (not necessarily considered as valid species at present) was surely more than five hundred.
</paragraph>
